  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n`cluster-name` is used by servicecontroller and routecontroller, for controller-manager, we have an option to set it, but for cloud-controller-manager, it will always be of default value 'kubernetes'.\r\n\r\nHere are some examples where it was in use:\r\n\r\naws:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/6b39b017b4096028396719b062bf56c00ca8d7f3/pkg/cloudprovider/providers/aws/aws_routes.go#L69\r\n\r\nazure:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/a5f766063ddb668f7a8dc924a20fe8e4bb441a37/pkg/cloudprovider/providers/azure/azure_util.go#L186\r\n\r\ngce:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/80ea31fcbf1a416a7d380582a7139f4132e3fece/pkg/cloudprovider/providers/gce/gce_routes.go#L43\r\n\r\nopenstack\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/eb86cc5e87c077fec088bc6061e4774344e5f5d9/pkg/cloudprovider/providers/openstack/openstack_loadbalancer.go#L904\r\n\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nHaving an option to set the value.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\n",
